[{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/4", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/4/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/4/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/4/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pull/4", "id": 3139773175, "node_id": "PR_kwDOH1SClc6aMNO0", "number": 4, "title": "Add Claude Code GitHub Workflow", "user": {"login": "foxzool", "id": 217027, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIxNzAyNw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/217027?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool", "html_url": "https://github.com/foxzool", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/foxzool/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2025-06-12T10:46:35Z", "updated_at": "2025-06-13T03:27:39Z", "closed_at": "2025-06-13T03:27:39Z", "author_association": "OWNER", "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pulls/4", "html_url": "https://github.com/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pull/4", "diff_url": "https://github.com/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pull/4.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pull/4.patch", "merged_at": "2025-06-13T03:27:39Z"}, "body": "## \ud83e\udd16 Installing Claude Code GitHub App\r\n\r\nThis PR adds a GitHub Actions workflow that enables Claude Code integration in our repository.\r\n\r\n### What is Claude Code?\r\n\r\n[Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code) is an AI coding agent that can help with:\r\n- Bug fixes and improvements  \r\n- Documentation updates\r\n- Implementing new features\r\n- Code reviews and suggestions\r\n- Writing tests\r\n- And more!\r\n\r\n### How it works\r\n\r\nOnce this PR is merged, we'll be able to interact with Claude by mentioning @claude in a pull request or issue comment.\r\nOnce the workflow is triggered, Claude will analyze the comment and surrounding context, and execute on the request in a GitHub action.\r\n\r\n### Important Notes\r\n\r\n- **This workflow won't take effect until this PR is merged**\r\n- **@claude mentions won't work until after the merge is complete**\r\n- The workflow runs automatically whenever Claude is mentioned in PR or issue comments\r\n- Claude gets access to the entire PR or issue context including files, diffs, and previous comments\r\n\r\n### Security\r\n\r\n- Our Anthropic API key is securely stored as a GitHub Actions secret\r\n- Only users with write access to the repository can trigger the workflow\r\n- All Claude runs are stored in the GitHub Actions run history\r\n- Claude's default tools are limited to reading/writing files and interacting with our repo by creating comments, branches, and commits.\r\n- We can add more allowed tools by adding them to the workflow file like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nallowed_tools: Bash(npm install),Bash(npm run build),Bash(npm run lint),Bash(npm run test)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere's more information in the [Claude Code documentation](http://docs.anthropic.com/s/claude-code-github-actions).\r\n\r\nAfter merging this PR, let's try mentioning @claude in a comment on any PR to get started!", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/4/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/4/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/3", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/3/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/3/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/3/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pull/3", "id": 2157725290, "node_id": "PR_kwDOH1SClc5oG0fc", "number": 3, "title": "Add 2 tests and CI", "user": {"login": "varoonp123", "id": 22409608, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyNDA5NjA4", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/22409608?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123", "html_url": "https://github.com/varoonp123", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/varoonp123/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2024-02-27T22:31:41Z", "updated_at": "2024-02-28T04:02:55Z", "closed_at": "2024-02-28T02:46:54Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pulls/3", "html_url": "https://github.com/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pull/3", "diff_url": "https://github.com/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pull/3.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/foxzool/bevy_serialport/pull/3.patch", "merged_at": "2024-02-28T02:46:54Z"}, "body": "The test basically boils down to:\r\n```rust\r\nuse bevy::prelude::*;\r\nlet mut app = App::new();\r\n// The app should only update for 10 ticks before exiting gracefully or panicking. Typically\r\n// calling .run() will never return, which is bad for a test and CI.\r\napp.add_plugins((MinimalPlugins, SerialPortPlugin))\r\n    .insert_resource(TestPTTYPortNames {\r\n        sender: String::from(serial_port_name),\r\n        receiver: String::from(serial_port_name2),\r\n    })\r\n    .add_systems(Startup, (setup_receiver, setup_sender))\r\n    .add_systems(PostStartup, send_test_data)\r\n    .add_systems(\r\n        Update,\r\n        poll_serial_messages_10_times_exit_app_if_found_else_panic,\r\n    );\r\napp.run(); // This should shut down if we received a serial signal.\r\n```\r\n\r\nOne smoke test can run basically anywhere bevy + serialport + tokio run. \r\n\r\nThe other is linux specific and uses [socat](https://www.redhat.com/sysadmin/getting-started-socat) to \"mock\" a linked device.   \r\n\r\nSince we use this lib in our game, I want to make sure it atleast compiles. ", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/foxzool/bevy_serialport/issues/3/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_